<font color="#FF0000">VETERANS RECOGNITION</font><br>
<tt>Thu May  1 22:04:45 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I have heard so much about the Vietnam situation, and how forgotten they were, and it grinds me when I think of how quickly everyone has put the Korean &quot;peace initiative&quot; behind them.  Yes, I was in the Korean &quot;thing&quot;, but they didn't build any wall to those who died there, and you sure as hell haven't heard much from those Vets.<br><br>
So what's the point???  Perhaps a reflecting wall that mirrors the Vietnam wall - I think it's wrong to treat WWII vets like saviors, forget the Korean vets, and now fawn all attentions on Vietnam vets.  A vet is a vet, and all either did lay down their lives for their country or at least were there and were willing to.  Vets should be treated like Vets!
<p><code>-- kennard_kaplan@compuserve.com  (Ken Kaplan) </code><p>


